name: cytidine deaminase
classes: Acting on carbon-nitrogen bonds, other than peptide bonds;
reaction: (1) cytidine + H2O = uridine + NH3 [RN:R01878]; (2) 2'-deoxycytidine + H2O = 2'-deoxyuridine + NH3 [RN:R02485]
comment: Contains zinc. Catalyses the deamination of cytidine and 2'-deoxycytidine with similar efficiencies. The enzyme, which is widely distributed among organisms, is involved in salvage of both exogenous and endogenous cytidine and 2'-deoxycytidine for UMP synthesis.
